    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get the reform thing, but some people argue that the whole structure itself is the problem and that it's basically just a tool for big countries to protect their own interests while doing nothing for everyone else. do historians see that as a valid critique of the UN's legitimacy, or is that usually seen as a fringe view?",
